premise_source_doc_sentence: Scream 3 performed critically worse than both its preceding films , receiving mixed reviews , but earned over $ 161 million ; many critics said that the film had become precisely what Scream originally spoofed .
Scream 3 fared worse than its predecessors , both critically and financially , with critics commenting that it had become the type of horror film it originally parodied in Scream .

The series is notable in the horror genre for casting established and popular actors which , before Scream  (  1996  )  , was uncommon and difficult , the genre not taken seriously by mainstream actors .
Scream 3 combines the violence of the slasher genre with comedy and `` whodunit '' mystery , while satirizing the cliché of film trilogies .

Drew Barrymore was originally cast as Sidney Prescott but scheduling conflicts led to her taking a smaller role , with the lead being offered instead to Campbell , who at the time was starring in the TV show Party of Five .
